Document: CSGPolygon3D
Path: godot/classes/class_csgpolygon3d.rst
Summary: Describes the purpose and performance considerations of CSGPolygon3D.

An array of 2D points is extruded to quickly and easily create a variety of 3D meshes. See also CSGMesh3D for using 3D meshes as CSG nodes.
Note: CSG nodes are intended to be used for level prototyping. Creating CSG nodes has a significant CPU cost compared to creating a MeshInstance3D with a PrimitiveMesh. Moving a CSG node within another CSG node also has a significant CPU cost, so it should be avoided during gameplay.
---CHUNK---
